These are the first records of this species since its original description (
Galiano, 1964a
). In 
Colombia
, the species was collected beating vegetation in a grassland near an intervened high Andean wet forest, and near to a road in a highly conserved Andean wet forest at the Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta (
Fig. 17
). There is an unconfirmed record of the species from 
Brazil
, Amazonas, Humaitá, Humaitá (SMNK 2901) listed by Heiko Meztner (Meztner, 2015; 
Fig. 19
).
